parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat backrest can cause the seat to collapse backwards while driving, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The driver's seat backrest collapses backwards
the bolts shearing off
the seat moves excessively while sitting
the seat backrest does not stay up on its own
the seat backrest falls backwards while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of a latch on the front seats can cause the seats to bend forward, potentially leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: No latch on front seats to prevent seats from bending forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the serpentine belt can cause loss of power, making it difficult to manage the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The serpentine belt slips from the pulley assembly
especially when in contact with water
causing loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls daily
despite replacing hoses
battery
filters
etc.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences sudden acceleration
even when not using cruise control
causing loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor repair work can cause additional problems, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle is returned to the customer with more problems than before
and the dealer does not accept responsibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motor mounts can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The motor mounts fall off the vehicle while in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked rear axle can cause the vehicle to flex and lose control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle stability.
symptoms: Clanging noise near the axle area
vehicle flexes when placed under strain during normal driving conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with the transmission gear selector can cause the vehicle to shift gears without the driver's input, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Automatic transmission shifts gears without pressing the button
can remove keys from ignition without gear in park position
can shift gears without ignition switch turned.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning speedometer can cause the driver to be unaware of their speed, leading to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: Speedometer failure
inaccurate speed readings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hatchback lift gate struts can cause the lift gate to fall, resulting in injury to the owner or occupants, and potentially causing damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The hatchback lift gate falls or does not stay in the open position
requiring propping with an object to keep it open
and in some cases
causing injury to the owner or occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The peeling and rusting of the paint can lead to rust damage, corrosion, and potentially affect the structural integrity of the vehicle.
symptoms: Paint peeling and flaking off
exposing bare metal
and in some cases
rusting has occurred.
